01. In this tutorial, we'll learn about Mutability and Private Members. 
02. Since scala prefers variables and classes to be immutable, we'll make Student class Immutable here.
03. If a variable in a class is declared as var then its object can change its value from anywhere which is bad.
04. But if we still want to modify that value within the class and prevent its value getting changed from other class then use "private var"
